fields.description:
I am facing issues while want to publish or test application in Android platform. I have Android SDK already selected in it. But that is not working in Appcelerator I think. In Android Studio that SDK works well as expected. So I am attaching every possible logs and screen-shot that help us. 
Please give me guidence that any issue from my side still exists for implement.

I have also tried with downgrad and Upgrade CLI and SDK version but faced same issues in it.

Thanks & Best Regards,
Abidhusain.
fields.summary: Unable to build project in Android after updating MacOS Mojave(10.14) & Re-Install fresh Appcelerator Studio

Hello, Sometimes when you install Android SDK through studio this type of issue occurs. You can download the Android SDK package in here http://dl.google.com/android/android-sdk_r21.1-macosx.zip. Now, put the unzip folder in a root directory and configure the directory in your studio by studio/preference/studio/platforms/android/ Android SDK home. Close studio. Go to your Android SDK folder/tools/android. This will open the Android SDK manager. Download and install the recommended SDK tools and build tools. Now restart the pc after the installation is done. Now check again in the studio. Android SDK should be configured. Let us know. Thanks.
I tried several time with replacing tools that you provide and steps that you mentioned. But not working currently. It worked for single time when I placed initially after that not working yet.
Hello, Can you run a project through terminal? Try to run with terminal from the project directory "appc run -p android", check the log. Send it here is the issue still there. Thanks.
